CONJECTURE (verbatim, OpenReview v6Ulp3U1ZT, Conjecture 6.1): "If P is a simple
3-polytope with face vector (p3, p4, . . . , pm), such that sum_{k>=7} pk >= 3,
then p6 >= 39/20 + p3/2 - p5/4 - sum_{k>=7} pk."
Integer violation test used (p6 integral, S := sum_{k>=7} pk):
    S >= 3  AND  20*p6 < 39 + 10*p3 - 5*p5 - 20*S

GENERATOR: plantri 5.8, downloaded fresh from
https://users.cecs.anu.edu.au/~bdm/plantri/plantri58.tar.gz
sha256(plantri58.tar.gz) = e78a944116fec9f2c9f5e484206276cc2b0043bae803e9815f4b2683614629b8
Built in WSL Ubuntu with: gcc -O3 -o plantri plantri.c
Exact invocation per n:  plantri -a <n>  |  rederive_filter
plantri default class (manual plantri-guide.txt, "SELECTING THE GRAPH CLASS"):
  "-c3m3 (default)  3-connected plane triangulation.
       The dual is a 3-connected plane cubic graph.
       Both primal and dual graphs are simple."
i.e. exactly the simple planar triangulations whose duals are, by Steinitz's
theorem, the graphs of simple 3-polytopes.

DUAL-DEGREE EQUIVALENCE: pk(polytope) = #{degree-k vertices of triangulation}.
