CERTIFICATE MATCHING (match_certs.py): canonical-form matching.  For each
embedded triangulation, the canonical code is the lexicographic minimum, over
all starting directed edges and both global orientations (mirror included),
of a BFS relabeling code of the rotation system; by Whitney's theorem this is
a complete isomorphism invariant for 3-connected planar graphs.
